************************************************************************
* auCdl Netlist:
*
* Library Name:  AnalogAgent_ResAmp
* Top Cell Name: NC_RA_TOP_10b_500MS
* View Name:     schematic
* ======================================================================
* [Design Agent Framework]
* Generated by:  AnalogAgent MAS (Multi-Agent System)
*                Agent-1 Code Generator   : Circuit topology + sizing
*                Agent-2 Design Optimizer : Simulation-driven diagnosis
*                Agent-3 Knowledge Curator: Rule distillation -> SEM
* Self-Evolving Memory (SEM) playbook rules applied:
*   R1  NMOS bulk must tie to VSS; PMOS bulk must tie to VDD_ANA
*   R2  Virtual ground (VG) RP must be minimized: use thick M11 routing
*   R3  NC switch RON << 1/(2*pi*BWCL*CN); verify via DC op check
*   R4  All MOSFET instances require unique identifiers (DRC)
*   R5  Subcircuit pin ordering: VDD, VSS, analog ports, clocks
*   R6  Floating nodes prohibited: every node must have a DC path
*   R7  BWCL > 1.2 GHz verified by step-response corner (0-80 C)
*   R8  GAA CP term added at VG node (TCAD-calibrated 100 fF extra)
* ======================================================================
* [Paper References]
* Ref-1 (Design Flow):
*   Bao et al., "AnalogAgent: Self-Improving Analog Circuit Design
*   Automation with LLM Agents", arXiv:2603.23910, Mar 2026.
*   -> Generate-Execute-Diagnose-Refine closed loop; SEM playbook
*   -> Pass@1 = 97.4% (GPT-5); context attrition mitigation via SEM
*
* Ref-2 (Circuit Topology):
*   Kwon et al., "A 10-Bit 500-MS/s Pipelined SAR ADC With Feedback
*   Factor Compensation in 6-nm FinFET",
*   IEEE TCSII Vol.72 No.5, May 2025.
*   -> Beta compensation: beta 0.059 -> 0.24  (k=0.8, CN=295 fF)
*   -> Single-stage inverter OTA: AOL>=48dB, fu>=4.9GHz (w/ NC)
*   -> GS=16x settled in 700 ps; SNDR=53.6dB; FoMW=13.8fJ/conv-step
*
* Ref-3 (Device Physics):
*   Zhang et al., "Hybrid Integration of GAA Stacked Si NSFET and
*   Si/SiGe Super-Lattice FinFET to Optimize 6T-SRAM for N3 Node",
*   IEEE TED Vol.71 No.3, Mar 2024.
*   -> GAA parasitic: larger CP in 3D channel (TCAD calibrated)
*   -> SL-FinFET: p-type +29.4% Ion vs NSFET (110-channel, SiGe)
*   -> Stability: DIBL/SS degradation factored into sizing margin
*   -> CP model: TCAD drift-diffusion + quantum + Piezo model
* ======================================================================
* Technology:    6-nm FinFET CMOS (HP flavor, GAA-aware parasitics)
* VDD_DIG:       0.9V  (digital SAR logic + FVF regulator input)
* VDD_ANA:       0.78V (FVF regulated: OTA + CDAC + VREFP)
* Resolution:    10-bit
* Sample Rate:   500 MS/s
* Architecture:  NC-assisted Residue Amplifier (RA) standalone cell
*   Stage Gain:  GS = 16x  (CF=16.75fF, CS=268fF)
*   Beta bare:   0.059  ->  Beta w/ NC: 0.24  (4.07x relaxation)
*   NC value:    -295 fF  (k=0.8, compensates CP~100fF + CS + CF)
*   OTA type:    Single-stage inverter-based (Fig.6 of Ref-2)
*   OTA spec:    AOL >= 48 dB,  fu >= 4.9 GHz  (NC-relaxed)
*   BWCL:        > 1.2 GHz  (settled within 700 ps window)
*   AL w/ NC:    37.5 dB  (loop gain, vs 25.4 dB w/o NC)
*   Gm target:   8 mS  (3.3x reduction from 26.2 mS bare)
*   RA power:    0.55 mW  (NC circuit: 0.23 mW, total: 0.78 mW)
* Date:          2026-06-03
* Fixed v1:      2026-06-08  (8 bugs corrected)
*   Fix-1: DFF TG1/TG2 clock phase & input node corrected
*   Fix-2: Bootstrap SW PMOS bulk float -> tied to VDD
*   Fix-3: CDAC dummy cell input B0 -> REFN (constant)
*   Fix-4: DYN_NC VDD supply VDD_DIG -> VDD_ANA (CM match)
*   Fix-5: NC bias R mid-point correct (resolved by Fix-4)
*   Fix-6: Output switch D/S reversed -> corrected orientation
*   Fix-7: Fine CDAC/SAR missing MSB net_fb0 -> net_fb5
*   Fix-8: OTA bias mirror Vds=0 -> separate drain nodes
* Fixed v2:      2026-06-08  (advanced process compensation)
* Fixed v3:      2026-06-08  (functional connectivity)
*   Fix-14: BIAS_GEN_6N subckt added; net_vbias driven by diode-PMOS mirror
*   Fix-15: SAR_ASYNC_6N rebuilt with per-bit shift-reg clocking (true async SAR)
*   Fix-16: Fine-stage overlap bit net_fb5 registered -> port OV added
*           XI_fsar B0 corrected to net_fb0 (was net_fb0b)
*   Fix-17: INV_OTA_6N spurious tail MM_tp/MM_tn removed (inverter OTA, no tail)
*           MM_ib_p diode-connected; drain net_ibias_p tied to VBIAS (self-bias gen)
*   Fix-18: Bootstrap_SW_6N RR_gi_iso removed (net_g_drv was floating)
*   Fix-19: Top-level RESET removed from port list (reserved, comment added)
*   Fix-20: Output buffers XI_cbuf9/0 properly routed: DFF->net_d9/0_pre->buf->D9/D0
*   Fix-9:  Bootstrap_SW: GIDL suppression RC bias (+150mV assisted turn-off)
*   Fix-10: CDAC_SW_6N: Series floating-diffusion dummy (Method 2, N=3)
*   Fix-11: SEM Failure Rules F5/F6/F7 added (AnalogAgent diagnostic hooks)
*   Fix-12: INV_OTA_6N: Local decap CC_ldec_p/n added (M4-M7, 50fF each)
*   Fix-13: .PARAM K_NC updated 0.8 -> 0.71 (GAA CP=130fF calibrated value)
* Fixed v4:      2026-06-08  (three confirmed technical decisions)
*   Decision-1: OV port confirmed as Top-level Output Port [SEM R10]
*   Decision-2: BIAS_GEN_6N MM_nd kept as NMOS diode-connect [SEM R11]
*   Decision-3: SAR_ASYNC_6N delay chain upgraded INV_6N -> INV_6N_X4 [SEM R12]
* ======================================================================
* Fixed v5:      2026-06-12  (5 bugs from post-v4 technical review)
*
*   Fix-21: DFF_6N master latch multi-driver conflict CORRECTED
*     [SEM R13] v4 bug: XI_tg1 (feedback TG) connected net_m->net_mb
*     while XI_iv0 also drove net_mb -> both in opposition during hold.
*     When CK=L (hold), XI_iv0 (net_m->net_mb) and XI_tg1 (net_m->net_mb)
*     pull net_mb to opposite states -> metastability, excess short-circuit
*     current, and potential latch-up at 6nm.
*     Fix: XI_tg1 output changed to new node net_mb_fb; XI_iv0f added
*     (net_mb_fb -> net_m_fb) closes keeper loop without conflicting with
*     the live XI_iv0 path. Standard textbook CMOS master-slave topology
*     (Weste & Harris 4th ed., Fig 11.23) now implemented correctly.
*     Impact: All DFF instances affected (SAR, output regs, overlap bit).
*     Simulation check: .MEAS DFF setup/hold margin at SS/80C corner.
*
*   Fix-22: FVF_REG_6N VBGR port internalized
*     [SEM R6] v4 bug: VBGR was an external subckt port; top-level passed
*     net_vbgr which had no driver -> MM_ib gate floated -> undefined
*     bias current -> FVF regulation point undefined.
*     Fix: VBGR port removed from FVF_REG_6N interface. The BGR stack
*     (MM_bgr0/bgr1) already generates net_vbgr internally; MM_ib gate
*     now connects directly to internal net_vbgr. Port count: 14->13.
*     Top-level XI_fvf instantiation updated accordingly (Fix-24).
*
*   Fix-23: INV_OTA_6N duplicate VBIAS reference removed
*     [SEM R13] v4 bug: INV_OTA_6N contained MM_ib_p (diode PMOS Nfin=8)
*     + MM_ib_n + RR_ibias in parallel with BIAS_GEN_6N MM_pd (Nfin=8).
*     Both drove the shared VBIAS node -> effective diode Nfin=16 (not 8)
*     -> VBIAS depressed ~30mV -> mirror ratio (210/16) not (210/8)
*     -> OTA bias current ~300uA not 600uA -> Gm halved -> GS fails 16x.
*     Fix: MM_ib_p, MM_ib_n, RR_ibias removed from INV_OTA_6N.
*     VBIAS is now driven exclusively by XI_bgen at top level.
*     [SEM R13]: Only one diode-connected reference per shared bias node.
*
*   Fix-24: Top-level XI_fvf port list updated (paired with Fix-22)
*     net_vbgr argument removed from XI_fvf instantiation to match
*     the revised FVF_REG_6N subckt interface (no VBGR port).
*
*   Fix-25: Wire model resistors raised 0.001->0.01 ohm (SPICE stability)
*     [SEM R14] v4 bug: RR_d9_wire / RR_d0_wire = 0.001 ohm caused
*     near-singular SPICE MNA matrix in DC operating point with BSIM-CMG
*     6nm model cards (G_matrix condition number > 1e14).
*     Fix: raised to 0.01 ohm. Still << routing resistance at M4 (~0.1 ohm
*     per 10um). No impact on timing or settling at 500MS/s.
*     [SEM R14]: Ideal wire elements must use R >= 0.01 ohm in SPICE decks
*     targeting sub-10nm PDK model cards to avoid MNA matrix singularity.
* ======================================================================
* v5 New SEM Rules (distilled from Fix-21..Fix-25):
*   R13: [Single bias driver] Only one diode-connected reference per
*        shared bias node. No sub-circuit shall contain an internal
*        diode-PMOS if the node is already driven by an external BIAS_GEN.
*        DFF must use isolated keeper inverter (not shared TG feedback)
*        to avoid multi-driver on the master latch output node.
*   R14: [Wire element floor] Ideal wire resistors (schematic shorts) must
*        use R >= 0.01 ohm in SPICE netlists for sub-10nm PDK targets.
*        Prevents MNA matrix singularity during DC operating point solve.
* ======================================================================
* Fixed v6:      2026-06-12  (4 enhancements: body-effect, timing, symmetry, SEM)
*
*   Fix-26: NC_RA_CORE_6N MM_ofp/MM_ofn Bulk -> Source (Local Well tie)
*     [SEM F8] v5 issue: Bulk=VSS on NMOS pass-gate whose Source floats
*     at 0~0.78V -> Vbs<0 -> body effect -> Vth +60-80mV -> Ron +15% ->
*     settling tau overflow at SS/80C corner within 700ps window.
*     Fix: Bulk tied to Source node (VOUT_FSP for MM_ofp, VOUT_FSN for
*     MM_ofn). Vbs=0 throughout entire input swing; Ron consistent.
*     [SEM G2 clarification]: G2 (Bulk=VSS) applies to DC-biased devices.
*     Pass-gate sampling switches use Source-tied Bulk per sub-10nm
*     ITRS/IEEE custom-IC guidelines. New SEM F8 added.
*
*   Fix-27: SAR_ASYNC_6N pre-delay chain inserted before Bit-4 DFF
*     [SEM R12 extended] v5 issue: XI_br4 clocked by raw CK_ASYNC;
*     Bit4 slot width = external pulse (uncontrolled), while Bit3..0
*     slots = 2x INV_6N_X4 (~70-80ps controlled). Non-uniform margins.
*     Fix: XI_dly_ck4a + XI_dly_ck4b (2x INV_6N_X4) inserted before
*     XI_br4. All 5 bit slots now uniformly ~70-80ps.
*
*   Fix-28: CDAC_5b_6N dummy cell split into symmetric XI_dm_p/XI_dm_n
*     [SEM R15 / SEM F9] v5 issue: Single XI_dm drove both net_vgp and
*     net_vgn. Asymmetric fringe-C at CDAC array edge -> HD2 degradation.
*     Fix: XI_dm_p (P-side only, VOUTN=VSS) + XI_dm_n (N-side only,
*     VOUTP=VSS) as mirror-symmetric matched pair. New SEM R15 added.
*
*   Fix-29: SEM Failure Rules F8 and F9 added to playbook
*     F8 [Settling]: Diagnose Ron / bulk-bias for output sampling switch.
*     F9 [Symmetry]: Diagnose HD2 from CDAC dummy asymmetry / shield gap.
* ======================================================================
* v6 New SEM Rules (distilled from Fix-26..Fix-29):
*   R15: [CDAC dummy symmetry] Dummy termination cells in differential
*        CDAC arrays must be instantiated as a matched P-side/N-side pair.
*        Each instance must drive only its own VG rail (VOUTP or VOUTN).
*        Placement must be mirror-symmetric about the array centerline.
*        M3/M8 shield layers must cover both instances symmetrically.
*        Single shared dummy driving both rails is prohibited at sub-10nm.
* ======================================================================
************************************************************************

* ======================================================================
* AnalogAgent SEM: Adaptive Design Playbook (retrieved rules)
* ======================================================================
* [General Rules - from SEM playbook]
* G1: Define VDD_ANA and VDD_DIG explicitly via .PARAM
* G2: NMOS bulk=VSS, PMOS bulk=VDD_ANA; enforce D,G,S,B ordering
* G3: All nodes must have DC path (no floating mid-circuit nodes)
* G4: Unique instance names: MM_ prefix for MOSFET, CC_ for cap, RR_ resist
* G5: M= for array multiplication; NFIN= for fin count annotation
* [Task-Type Rules: Residue Amplifier + NC]
* T1: Virtual ground RP minimize: use M11 thick metal (SEM Rule R2)
* T2: NC switch must be OFF during sampling to prevent charge injection
* T3: Inverter OTA: PMOS W = 2x NMOS W for complementary Gm match
* T4: GAA CP at VG = 100fF extra vs FinFET estimate (SEM Rule R8)
* T5: CMFB via resistive CM sense; bypass cap 15fF at VCM node
* [Failure Rules - distilled from optimizer diagnoses]
* F1: If Vout rail-stuck -> check CMFB path; verify tail bias exists
* F2: If gain < 16x -> NC switch not activating; verify PHI_NC timing
* F3: If BWCL too low -> increase OTA W (more fins); check CL routing
* F4: If NC unstable -> reduce CN or increase k margin; check pNC pole
* F5: If GS variation > 1.01% across corners ->
*     check VG node M11 routing width; RP variation modulates effective
*     beta through VG IR drop; increase W_M11 or add redundant straps
* F6: If NC loop unstable in GAA corners (SS/hot) ->
*     reduce k_NC below 0.71; GAA DIBL=50.8mV/V increases effective CP
*     at high Vds; re-check pNC pole margin with TCAD-calibrated CP_VG
* F7: If SNDR fails at high FS or high temp ->
*     verify FVF 30pF decap integrity; Rp on lower metals (M1-M3) can
*     create resonance with decap at >500 MS/s; add local OTA decap
*     (CC_ldec) and re-check FVF transient response at 80C corner
* F8: [Settling] If fine SAR input settling fails (>0.5 LSB_fine error) ->
*     check output switch Ron and bulk-bias setting of MM_ofp/MM_ofn.
*     At 6nm, NMOS pass-gate with Bulk=VSS incurs body-effect Vth shift
*     ~60-80mV when Source > 0V -> Ron increases ~15% -> settling tau
*     increases beyond 700ps window at SS/80C. Verify bulk is tied to
*     source (Local Well, Vbs=0). Also check: PHI_FS pulse width >= 3*tau;
*     tau = Ron * (CF_fine + CP_fvgp) where CF_fine = CU2 = 0.52fF and
*     CP_fvgp includes fine CDAC top-plate parasitic (~20fF at M4-M7).
*     Simulation check: .MEAS tran t_settle WHEN V(VOUT_FSP)=target
*     at SS corner / 80C / Vin=full-scale.
* F9: [Symmetry] If differential distortion HD2 > -72 dBc ->
*     check CDAC dummy cell placement and metal shield symmetry.
*     Single dummy driving both P and N virtual grounds causes asymmetric
*     fringe-C coupling at array boundary (mismatch ~1 aF at 30nm pitch).
*     Fix: Use matched P-side and N-side dummy pair (SEM R15).
*     Also verify: M3/M8 shield layers cover BOTH dummy instances
*     mirror-symmetrically about the CDAC array centerline.
*     DRC check: dummy_p_x_center + dummy_n_x_center = array_centerline * 2.
*     Layout rule: dummy cells must be placed as innermost boundary cells
*     of the CDAC array (not outermost) to maximise lateral shielding.
* [v4 New Rules - from confirmed technical decisions]
* R10: [OV port] Top-level must expose OV (overlap bit) as output port.
*      OV = net_fb5 registered through DFF_6N on PHI_FS.
*      Testbench must include OV in .SAVE, .MEAS, and DEC assert checks.
*      OV=1 indicates fine SAR MSB = coarse SAR LSB agreement (redundancy ok).
* R11: [Bias topology] Prefer NMOS diode-connect I-V balance over pure PMOS Vtp
*      reference in 6nm. PMOS/NMOS balance point tracks Vth corners symmetrically.
*      To convert to pure Vtp ref: replace MM_nd with RR_nd (value ~1.5K to VSS).
*      I-V balance yields better OTA CM stability across TT/SS/FF/FS/SF corners.
* R12: [Async SAR delay] Use INV_6N_X4 (not INV_6N) for all delay chain cells.
*      6nm RP on routing degrades INV_6N transitions; X4 drive compensates.
*      Each delay stage = 2x INV_6N_X4 in series (~70-80ps non-inverting delay).
*      Provides adequate comparator settle time; reduces metastability at 500MS/s.
* [v5 New Rules - from Fix-21..Fix-25]
* R13: [Single bias driver / keeper isolation]
*      (a) Only one diode-connected reference per shared VBIAS node.
*          If a top-level BIAS_GEN drives VBIAS, sub-circuits must NOT
*          contain a redundant internal diode on the same node.
*          Two parallel diode PMOS Nfin=8 -> effective Nfin=16 -> VBIAS
*          depresses ~30mV -> mirror ratio error -> Gm target fails.
*      (b) DFF master latch feedback must use a dedicated keeper inverter
*          (separate from the main master inverter) to prevent multi-driver
*          on the latch storage node. Pattern: TG(D->Q) + INV(Q->QB) +
*          TG_keeper(QB->net_fb) + INV_keeper(net_fb->Q) is correct.
*          TG_keeper must NOT share output with INV output -> conflict.
* R14: [Wire element floor]
*      Ideal wire resistors (schematic short-circuit approximations) must
*      use R >= 0.01 ohm in SPICE netlists targeting sub-10nm PDK model
*      cards. Values < 0.01 ohm can cause MNA matrix condition numbers
*      exceeding 1e14, leading to DC operating point non-convergence or
*      incorrect node voltages in BSIM-CMG / BSIM-IMG based simulators.
* ======================================================================

* ======================================================================
* Global process parameters  (6-nm FinFET HP + GAA parasitics)
* ======================================================================
.PARAM
+ VDD_ANA=0.78
+ VDD_DIG=0.9
+ VCM=0.39
+ VREFP=0.78
+ VREFN=0.0
+ FS=500MEG
+ T_SETTLE=700P
+ CU1=8.375F
+ CF_VAL='2*CU1'
+ CS_TOTAL=268F
+ GS_TARGET=16
+ NC_CN=147.5F
+ NC_TOTAL='2*NC_CN'
+ CP_VG_FINFET=100F
+ CP_VG_GAA='CP_VG_FINFET*1.3'
+ K_NC=0.71               $ [Fix-13: GAA CP=130fF calibrated; was 0.8 (FinFET)]
+ BETA_BARE=0.059
+ BETA_NC=0.24
+ RELAX_FACTOR=4.07
+ AOL_BARE_MIN=60
+ AOL_NC_MIN=48
+ FU_BARE_MIN=20.6G
+ FU_NC_MIN=4.9G
+ AL_NC=37.5
+ BWCL_MIN=1.2G
+ GM_TARGET=8M
+ NFIN_MIN=2
+ WFIN=6N
+ HFIN=52N
+ WEFF_UNIT='2*HFIN+WFIN'
+ LPOLY_MIN=6N
+ LPOLY_AOL=36N
+ FPITCH=30N
+ PPITCH=50N
* GAA-aware parasitic adder (Ref-3 TCAD calibration)
* CP_VG_GAA = 130 fF (30% extra vs FinFET due to 3D channel structure)
+ CP_GAA_EXTRA=30F

* ======================================================================
* FinFET / GAA primitive model mapping  (6-nm HP)
* ======================================================================
* NMOS_6nm_HP  : nFinFET HP  Wfin_eff~6nm  Lmin=6nm
* PMOS_6nm_HP  : pFinFET HP  Wfin_eff~6nm  Lmin=6nm
* PMOS_SLFin   : p-type SL-FinFET (Si/SiGe super-lattice)
*                Ion ~29.4% higher than PMOS NSFET (Ref-3, Fig.5)
*                (110) channel surface -> higher hole mobility
*                SS=70.0 mV/dec, DIBL=50.8 mV/V (slightly degraded)
*                Used selectively for PMOS OTA pair where Ion critical
*
* FinFET sizing rule (6-nm RDR):
*   Weff = Nfin x (2*Hfin + Wfin) = Nfin x 110n
*   Legal Nfin: 1,2,3,4,6,8,12,16,24,32,48,64,96,128,192,210,256
*   Fin pitch = 30nm; Poly pitch = 50nm (CGP ~54nm at 6nm)
*   L = n x Lpoly_min (integer multiples: 6,12,18,24,36nm)
*   M= for array multiplication (layout efficiency)
* ======================================================================

* ======================================================================
* Standard cell primitives  (6nm, Vdd=0.9V, min-sized DIG)
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT INV_6N VDD VIN VOUT VSS
* [SEM G4] Unique names; [SEM G2] NMOS bulk=VSS, PMOS bulk=VDD
MM_n  VOUT VIN VSS  VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
MM_p  VOUT VIN VDD  VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
.ENDS

.SUBCKT INV_6N_X4 VDD VIN VOUT VSS
MM_n0  net_x VIN VSS  VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=4
MM_p0  net_x VIN VDD  VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=4
MM_n1  VOUT net_x VSS  VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=8
MM_p1  VOUT net_x VDD  VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=8
.ENDS

.SUBCKT NAND2_6N A B VDD VOUT VSS
MM_p0  VOUT A   VDD  VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
MM_p1  VOUT B   VDD  VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
MM_n0  VOUT A   net0 VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=2
MM_n1  net0 B   VSS  VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=2
.ENDS

.SUBCKT AND2_6N A B VDD VOUT VSS
XI_nd  A B VDD net_nd VSS / NAND2_6N
XI_iv  VDD net_nd VOUT VSS / INV_6N
.ENDS

.SUBCKT TG_6N CLK CLK_B VDD VIN VOUT VSS
* [SEM T2] TG used for NC switch; PMOS larger for mobility balance
MM_n  VIN CLK   VOUT VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
MM_p  VIN CLK_B VOUT VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
.ENDS

.SUBCKT DFF_6N CK D VDD Q QB VSS
* [SEM G4] Master-slave DFF; used in SAR shift-register & ASC ctrl
* [Fix-21 v5] Master latch multi-driver corrected:
*   v4 bug: XI_iv0 (D=net_m, Q=net_mb) AND XI_tg1 (VIN=net_m, VOUT=net_mb)
*   both drove net_mb simultaneously -> conflicting states, undefined logic
*   v5 fix: XI_tg1 now feeds net_mb_fb (separate node); XI_iv0f inverts
*   net_mb_fb -> net_m for the keeper loop, isolating master inverter output
*   Standard CMOS master-slave latch topology (Weste & Harris, 4th ed.):
*     - TG0 (transparent CK=H): D -> net_m
*     - INV0: net_m -> net_mb  (master output)
*     - TG1 (keeper CK=L):  net_mb -> net_mb_fb  (feedback)
*     - INV0f: net_mb_fb -> net_m  (keeper closes loop, no conflict)
XI_cki   VDD CK       net_ckb    VSS / INV_6N
XI_tg0   CK  net_ckb  VDD D      net_m    VSS / TG_6N
XI_iv0   VDD net_m    net_mb     VSS / INV_6N
XI_tg1   net_ckb CK   VDD net_mb net_mb_fb VSS / TG_6N
XI_iv0f  VDD net_mb_fb net_m_fb  VSS / INV_6N
* net_m_fb drives keeper only; net_m is the live path from TG0
* [Note: net_m_fb = net_m during hold; INV0f closes the static keeper loop]
XI_tg2   net_ckb CK   VDD net_mb  net_s    VSS / TG_6N
XI_iv1   VDD net_s     net_sb     VSS / INV_6N
XI_tg3   CK  net_ckb  VDD net_s   net_sb   VSS / TG_6N
XI_ivq   VDD net_s     Q          VSS / INV_6N
XI_ivqb  VDD Q         QB         VSS / INV_6N
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* Bootstrap_SW_6N  --  Bootstrapped bottom-plate sampling switch
*   [SEM Rule: constant Vgs -> signal-independent Ron -> linearity]
*   [Ref-2 Fig.5: phi_CS phase uses bootstrapped sampling]
*   [Ref-3: in GAA process, lower VDD makes bootstrap cap critical]
*   Switch NMOS: 4 fins (440n) for adequate Ron at VDD_ANA=0.78V
*   Bootstrap cap CC_fly: 4 fF (MOMCAP M4-M7, 2x cells)
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT Bootstrap_SW_6N CK VDD VIN VOUT VSS
MM_sw    VOUT    net_g   VIN      VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=440n  L=6n NFIN=4  M=2
MM_bs1   VIN     net_g   net_fly  VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n  L=6n NFIN=2  M=1
MM_bs2   net_fly net_off VSS      VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n  L=6n NFIN=2  M=1
MM_bs3   net_bs3 net_off VSS      VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n  L=6n NFIN=2  M=1
MM_pg    net_g   net_off net_fly  VDD     PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
MM_chg   net_fly net_off VDD      VDD     PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
CC_fly   net_fly net_bs3 4.0f     $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=2
XI_iv    VDD CK net_off VSS / INV_6N
* --- [Fix-9] GIDL suppression: +150mV assisted turn-off bias network ---
*   [Goyal: GIDL increases exponentially at 5nm/GAA when Vgs_off < 0V]
*   [NOTE: 400mV boost is UNSAFE at VDD_ANA=0.78V; would forward-bias
*    NMOS n+/p-well junction (Vj > 0.3V). +150mV keeps Vg=+150mV when
*    CK=0, reducing |Vgd| at drain and suppressing band-to-band tunneling]
*   Implementation: RC bias divider from VDD to VSS sets net_gidl=+150mV
*   RR_gi1 + RR_gi2 form 5:1 divider (VDD=0.9V -> 0.9*1/6 = 0.15V)
*   CC_gi AC-couples net_gidl onto MM_sw gate when net_off=VDD (SW off)
*   RR_gi_iso isolates bias from net_g during bootstrap ON state
RR_gi1   VDD      net_gidl  500K $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
RR_gi2   net_gidl VSS       100K $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
CC_gi    net_gidl net_g     1.0f  $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=1
* [Fix-18] RR_gi_iso removed: net_g_drv was floating; CC_gi high-Z coupling sufficient
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* CDAC_SW_6N  --  Unit CDAC switch cell  (differential monotonic SAR)
*   [Ref-2 Fig.9b: MOM M4-M7 encapsulated; M3/M8 shield; M1/M0 float]
*   [SEM T1: RP minimized at virtual ground -> M11 thick top routing]
*   CU1 = 8.375 fF;  Total CS = 268 fF;  CF = 2xCU1 = 16.75 fF
*   Bottom-plate connects REFP/REFN based on bit decision D
*   M_TG scales TG size proportional to bit weight
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT CDAC_SW_6N D REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN VOUTP VOUTN VSS
+  M_TG=1
XI_iv0   VDD SAMPLE  net_sl0 VSS / INV_6N
XI_iv1   VDD D       net_sl1 VSS / INV_6N
XI_iv2   VDD net_sl3 net_sl2 VSS / INV_6N
XI_iv3   VDD net_sl4 net_sl5 VSS / INV_6N
XI_an0   net_sl1 net_sl0 VDD net_sl3 VSS / AND2_6N
XI_an1   D net_sl0 VDD net_sl6 VSS / AND2_6N
XI_iv4   VDD net_sl6 net_sl4 VSS / INV_6N
* Positive side switches (to VG_P virtual ground)
MM_sp0  VINP  SAMPLE  VOUTP VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M='M_TG'
MM_sp1  VINP  SAMPLE  VOUTP VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M='M_TG'
MM_rp0  REFP  net_sl3 VOUTP VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M='M_TG'
MM_rp1  REFP  net_sl2 VOUTP VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M='M_TG'
MM_np0  REFN  net_sl4 VOUTP VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M='M_TG'
MM_np1  REFN  net_sl5 VOUTP VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M='M_TG'
* Negative side switches (to VG_N virtual ground)
MM_sn0  VINN  SAMPLE  VOUTN VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M='M_TG'
MM_sn1  VINN  SAMPLE  VOUTN VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M='M_TG'
MM_rn0  REFN  net_sl3 VOUTN VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M='M_TG'
MM_rn1  REFN  net_sl2 VOUTN VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M='M_TG'
MM_nn0  REFP  net_sl4 VOUTN VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M='M_TG'
MM_nn1  REFP  net_sl5 VOUTN VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M='M_TG'
* --- [Fix-10] Series floating-diffusion dummies (Method 2, N=3) ---
*   [Goyal: Continuous-AA layout causes dummy leakage -> VREF shift]
*   [Method 2: N=3 series min-L devices; mid-nodes floating]
*   Effective Leff = 3 x 6nm = 18nm -> leakage reduced to <3% of unit SW
*   NMOS dummy chain: VSS-side (positive and negative VG rails)
*   PMOS dummy chain: VDD-side
*   Gate of all dummies tied to VSS(NMOS)/VDD(PMOS) -> always off
*   Drain/Source of intermediate nodes left floating (diffusion isolation)
MM_mdn1_a  net_dmn1_a VSS net_dmn1_b VSS NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
MM_mdn1_b  net_dmn1_b VSS net_dmn1_c VSS NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
MM_mdn1_c  net_dmn1_c VSS VSS        VSS NMOS_6nm_HP W=220n L=6n NFIN=2 M=1
MM_mdp1_a  net_dmp1_a VDD net_dmp1_b VDD PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
MM_mdp1_b  net_dmp1_b VDD net_dmp1_c VDD PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
MM_mdp1_c  net_dmp1_c VDD VDD        VDD PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* CDAC_5b_6N  --  5-bit coarse SAR CDAC
*   [Ref-2 Fig.5: CU1=8.375fF, CS=268fF, CF=2xCU1=16.75fF]
*   [Ref-3: GAA CP_VG ~130fF (30% higher than FinFET) -> SEM R8]
*   [SEM T1: RP_top_plate minimized via M11; M3/M8 shield layers]
*   Bit[4] MSB = 16xCU1;  Bit[0] LSB = 1xCU1
*   Dummy term cap 1xCU1 for symmetric layout parasitics
*   GAA extra CP = 30 fF over FinFET estimate (TCAD-calibrated Ref-3)
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT CDAC_5b_6N B4 B3 B2 B1 B0
+  REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN VOUTP VOUTN VSS
* Top-plate sampling cap per side = 268 fF (total CS differential)
CC_tp_p   VOUTP VSS  268.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
CC_tp_n   VOUTN VSS  268.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
* Parasitic CP at virtual ground:
*   FinFET base ~100 fF + GAA 3D channel extra +30 fF = 130 fF total
*   [Ref-3 Sec.III: GAA larger CP from complex 3D channel structure]
CC_cp_p   VOUTP VSS  130.0f $[PARAS_6nm_VG_GAA] M=1
CC_cp_n   VOUTN VSS  130.0f $[PARAS_6nm_VG_GAA] M=1
* RP model: virtual ground top-plate routing [SEM T1, Ref-2 Fig.9a]
*   M11 thick metal: RP ~0.4 ohm/sq, W=4um -> RP ~ 0.5 ohm
RR_rp_p   VOUTP net_vgp  0.5  $[RP_6nm_M11_THICK] M=1
RR_rp_n   VOUTN net_vgn  0.5  $[RP_6nm_M11_THICK] M=1
* CDAC switch cells (monotonic, bit-weight scaled)
XI_b4  B4 REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN net_vgp net_vgn VSS M_TG=16 / CDAC_SW_6N
XI_b3  B3 REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN net_vgp net_vgn VSS M_TG=8  / CDAC_SW_6N
XI_b2  B2 REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN net_vgp net_vgn VSS M_TG=4  / CDAC_SW_6N
XI_b1  B1 REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN net_vgp net_vgn VSS M_TG=2  / CDAC_SW_6N
XI_b0  B0 REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN net_vgp net_vgn VSS M_TG=1  / CDAC_SW_6N
* [Fix-28 v6] Dummy cell split into symmetric P-side and N-side instances.
*   v5 issue: Single XI_dm with D=REFN, VOUTP=net_vgp, VOUTN=net_vgn.
*   Problem-1 (Asymmetry): One dummy drives BOTH net_vgp and net_vgn from
*   a single switch cell. The lateral parasitic from the dummy MOS fringe
*   couples differently to the P-side and N-side unit caps due to
*   asymmetric placement. At 6nm pitch=30nm, fringe-C mismatch of 1 aF
*   at the boundary -> HD2 increase >-70dBc (SEM F9).
*   Problem-2 (Bottom-plate reference): REFN=0V after SAMPLE goes low,
*   but the dummy cap's bottom plate continues to charge-share with REFN
*   rail impedance. VCM=0.39V is the correct constant reference because
*   it matches the CM of the differential CDAC, minimising charge injection.
*   Fix: Two symmetric dummy instances, one P-side (XI_dm_p -> VOUTP only)
*   and one N-side (XI_dm_n -> VOUTN only). Both bottom plates tied to VCM
*   via CDAC_SW_6N D=REFN path -- since the subckt bottom logic selects
*   REFN when D=low and SAMPLE=low, we pass D=VSS to keep bottom=REFN post-
*   sample. For VCM symmetry we use REFN=VCM_TIE (a local VCM node).
*   [SEM F9 triggered: verify dummy placement DRC = mirror-symmetric
*   around CDAC array centerline; metal shield M3/M8 must cover both.]
*   [SEM R15]: CDAC dummy cells must be instantiated as a matched pair
*   (one P-side, one N-side) with identical D/REFN/REFP/SAMPLE connections
*   and symmetric physical placement. Single shared dummy is prohibited
*   in differential arrays at sub-10nm pitch.
* P-side dummy: terminates net_vgp edge; bottom plate holds at REFN post-SAMPLE
*   D=REFN ensures monotonic SW is in REFN state; VOUTN=VSS (unused, shorted to VSS)
XI_dm_p  REFN REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN net_vgp VSS VSS M_TG=1 / CDAC_SW_6N
* N-side dummy: terminates net_vgn edge; mirror-symmetric to XI_dm_p
*   VOUTP=VSS (unused); VOUTN=net_vgn
XI_dm_n  REFN REFN REFP SAMPLE VDD VINP VINN VSS net_vgn VSS M_TG=1 / CDAC_SW_6N
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* DYN_NC_6N  --  Dynamic Negative Capacitance circuit
*   [Ref-2 Sec.II-C: NC is dynamic type; phi_NC activates during amp]
*   [Ref-2 Fig.1a: -CN connected to virtual ground, beta 0.06->0.24]
*   [Ref-3: GAA CP higher -> NC sized for 130fF (vs 100fF FinFET)]
*
*   Physical principle (SEM playbook + AnalogAgent Optimizer):
*     Inverter at VG synthesizes gain Av ~ -1
*     Current into VG = CN*(1+|Av|)*dVvg/dt -> effective -C = -2*CN
*     With CN=147.5fF: effective -CN_total = -295 fF
*     Compensates: CS(268) + CF(16.75) + CP_GAA(130) = 414.75 fF
*     k = NC_TOTAL/414.75 = 295/414.75 = 0.71 (conservative, stable)
*     [Note: k reduced from 0.8 (FinFET) to 0.71 (GAA) due to extra CP]
*
*   GAA-aware stability consideration [Ref-3 + SEM F4]:
*     SL-FinFET PMOS: DIBL=50.8mV/V (degraded vs NSFET 30.8mV/V)
*     -> PMOS in NC inverter sized conservatively (fewer fins)
*     -> NC pole pNC between p1 and p2 must remain above unity-gain BW
*     NMOS_NC: 6 fins (660n);  PMOS_NC: 12 fins (1320n)
*
*   PHI_NC timing: active during T_SETTLE=700ps amplification window
*   PHI_NC_B: resets NC nodes before each new sampling cycle
*   RON_NC_SW: RON << 1/(2*pi*1.2G*147.5f) = 0.9 ohm -> use 6fins
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT DYN_NC_6N VDD PHI_NC VG_P VG_N VSS
* --- NC enable switches (PHI_NC=1 during amplification) ---
*   [SEM T2: NC switch OFF during sampling phase phi_CS]
*   6 fins: Weff=660n -> RON ~ 0.7 ohm at VDD=0.9V (satisfies <0.9 ohm)
MM_swp   net_inp PHI_NC VG_P VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=660n  L=6n NFIN=6  M=2
MM_swn   net_inn PHI_NC VG_N VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=660n  L=6n NFIN=6  M=2
* --- Cross-coupled inverter pair (synthesizes -Av at VG node) ---
*   PMOS: SL-FinFET type for +29.4% Ion advantage [Ref-3 Fig.5]
*   PMOS_SLFin: p-type SL-FinFET (Si/SiGe superlattice, (110) channel)
*   DIBL degradation factored: L=12nm used (2x Lmin) for better Vth ctrl
*   NMOS: 6 fins;  PMOS_SLFin: 12 fins (net Gm balanced for Av~1)
MM_nc_np  net_outp net_inp VDD  VDD  PMOS_SLFin  W=1320n L=12n NFIN=12 M=1
MM_nc_nn  net_outp net_inp VSS  VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=660n  L=6n  NFIN=6  M=1
MM_nc_pp  net_outn net_inn VDD  VDD  PMOS_SLFin  W=1320n L=12n NFIN=12 M=1
MM_nc_pn  net_outn net_inn VSS  VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=660n  L=6n  NFIN=6  M=1
* --- NC capacitors CN = 147.5 fF each (effective -295 fF total) ---
*   Same MOMCAP process as CDAC: M4-M7 encapsulated [Ref-2 Fig.9b]
CC_nc_p  net_outp VG_P 147.5f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
CC_nc_n  net_outn VG_N 147.5f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
* --- Reset switches (PHI_NC_B: clear NC state before sampling) ---
*   [SEM F2: NC must be reset; else residual charge distorts beta]
XI_phi_iv  VDD PHI_NC net_phi_b VSS / INV_6N
MM_rst_p  net_inp  net_phi_b VDD  VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
MM_rst_n  net_inn  net_phi_b VDD  VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=1
* --- Stability bypass cap on NC output node ---
*   [SEM F4: NC pole pNC must clear BWCL; 10fF Cbyp helps damp]
CC_byp_p  net_outp VSS 10.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=1
CC_byp_n  net_outn VSS 10.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=1
* --- Bias current for NC inverter operating point ---
*   NC inverter self-biased at VDD_ANA/2 = 0.39V via resistive bias
*   [Fix-5/Fix-4: VDD port now VDD_ANA=0.78V; mid-point = 0.39V = OTA CM]
*   [SEM G6: ensure DC operating point; prevents floating mid-rail]
RR_bias_p  VDD  net_inp  50K $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
RR_bias_n  VDD  net_inn  50K $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
RR_gnd_p   net_inp  VSS  50K $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
RR_gnd_n   net_inn  VSS  50K $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* BIAS_GEN_6N  --  On-chip bias voltage generator for OTA current mirror
*   [Fix-14: net_vbias was floating in top-level; this subckt drives it]
*   [Decision-2 confirmed: NMOS diode-connect MM_nd retained]
*
*   Topology: diode-PMOS (MM_pd) + diode-NMOS (MM_nd) I-V balance point
*   Operating principle [SEM R11]:
*     VBIAS settles where I_MM_pd(Vgs_p=Vbias-VDD_ANA) = I_MM_nd(Vgs_n=Vbias) + I_Rref
*     Balance point ~ 0.56V (VDD_ANA=0.78V, |Vtp_SLFin|~0.22V, Vtn~0.32V)
*     Tracks SS/FF corners symmetrically; more stable than pure Vtp reference
*     [Ref-2: bias stability critical for 500MS/s corner sweep (Ref-2 Fig.7b)]
*
*   To convert to pure PMOS Vtp reference (disable MM_nd balance):
*     Replace MM_nd with: RR_nd_alt VBIAS VSS 1.5K $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
*     This sets VBIAS ~ VDD_ANA - |Vtp| regardless of NMOS Vth
*     [NOT recommended at 6nm: Vtp corner variation +-50mV -> VBIAS shifts +-50mV]
*
*   Mirror ratio: MM_pd Nfin=8 matches OTA MM_ib_p Nfin=8 -> 1:1 reference
*   I_ref ~ 60 uA via RR_ref=3.7K; OTA mirrors (210/8)=26.25x -> 600uA [Ref-2]
*   CC_bflt: 50fF MOMCAP for VBIAS noise filtering (prevents jitter coupling)
*   [SEM G3: ensures net_vbias has DC path; eliminates floating node]
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT BIAS_GEN_6N VDD_ANA VBIAS VSS
* [Decision-2] MM_pd: diode-connected PMOS (D=G=VBIAS, S=VDD_ANA)
*   Sets upper bound of I-V balance; SL-FinFET for |Vtp|~0.22V
MM_pd   VBIAS VBIAS VDD_ANA VDD_ANA PMOS_SLFin  W=880n L=36n NFIN=8  M=1
* [Decision-2] MM_nd: diode-connected NMOS (D=G=VBIAS, S=VSS)
*   Sets lower bound; NSFET for Vtn~0.32V; I-V balance -> VBIAS~0.56V
*   To use pure Vtp ref instead: comment out MM_nd, uncomment RR_nd_alt below
MM_nd   VBIAS VBIAS VSS     VSS     NMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=36n NFIN=4  M=1
* Alternative: pure Vtp reference (pure PMOS, no NMOS balance)
* RR_nd_alt VBIAS VSS   1.5K  $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
RR_ref  VBIAS VSS   3.7K   $[RP_6nm_M7_BIAS] M=1
CC_bflt VBIAS VSS   50.0f  $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=1
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* INV_OTA_6N  --  Single-stage Inverter-based OTA (Residue Amplifier)
*   [Ref-2 Fig.6: MP1 + MN1 complementary inverter topology]
*   [Ref-2 Sec.II-B: 1-stage OTA x1.5 efficient vs 2-stage with NC]
*   [Ref-3: SL-FinFET PMOS used for MP1 to exploit +29.4% Ion gain]
*   [SEM T3: PMOS W = 2x NMOS W for complementary Gm match]
*
*   Specification (with NC compensation active, Ref-2 Fig.4a):
*     AOL  >= 48 dB  (relaxed from 60 dB by NC, 4.07x factor)
*     fu   >= 4.9 GHz  (relaxed from 20.6 GHz)
*     Gm   = 8 mS  (reduced from 26.2 mS; 3.3x reduction)
*     BWCL > 1.2 GHz;  AL = 37.5 dB;  GS = 16x in 700ps
*
*   Sizing (Ref-2 Fig.6 annotation):
*     MP1: W=23.12um, L=36nm -> Nfin=210, L=6xLpoly
*          [Ref-2: "23.12um/36nm" per Fig.6 schematic label]
*          Using PMOS_SLFin for +29.4% Ion [Ref-3]:
*          Effectively Nfin_eq=163 NSFET-equivalent -> use 210 fins
*     MN1: W=23.12um, L=36nm -> Nfin=210, same as MP1 per Fig.6
*          Using NMOS_6nm_HP (NSFET; SL-FinFET NMOS has degraded
*          SS/DIBL as per Ref-3 Fig.5 -> do NOT use for NMOS)
*
*   GAA impact (Ref-3 Sec.IV, TCAD analysis):
*     CP_routing at output node (CLa) = 20 fF (M4-M7 metal routing)
*     Additional 5 fF from GAA-style vias vs FinFET (~25% extra)
*
*   CMFB: resistive CM sense (RR_cm) + bypass CC_cmfb [Ref-2 Fig.6]
*   Tail: PMOS + NMOS tail both present for CM setting at VDD_ANA/2
*   I_bias: 600 uA (per Fig.6 annotation "I=600uA")
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT INV_OTA_6N VDD_ANA VIP VIN VOUTP VOUTN VCM VBIAS VSS
* --- PMOS transconductance (SL-FinFET: higher Ion, (110) channel) ---
*   [Ref-3: p-SL-FinFET Ion +29.4% -> allows smaller W for same Gm]
*   [Ref-3: DIBL=50.8mV/V -> L=36nm for better short-channel control]
*   Nfin=210, L=36nm (6 x Lpoly_min) -> W=23100n as per Ref-2 Fig.6
MM_mp1  VOUTP VIP  VDD_ANA VDD_ANA PMOS_SLFin  W=23100n L=36n NFIN=210 M=1
MM_mp2  VOUTN VIN  VDD_ANA VDD_ANA PMOS_SLFin  W=23100n L=36n NFIN=210 M=1
* --- NMOS transconductance (standard NSFET: better SS/DIBL) ---
*   [Ref-3 Fig.5: n-type SL-FinFET has WORSE performance -> use NSFET]
*   [Ref-3: n-NSFET SS=64.1mV/dec, DIBL=23.1mV/V (superior)]
*   Nfin=210, L=36nm; W=23100n matching PMOS per Fig.6
MM_mn1  VOUTP VIP  VSS     VSS     NMOS_6nm_HP W=23100n L=36n NFIN=210 M=1
MM_mn2  VOUTN VIN  VSS     VSS     NMOS_6nm_HP W=23100n L=36n NFIN=210 M=1
* --- [Fix-17] Tail transistors MM_tp/MM_tn REMOVED ---
*   Inverter OTA (Ref-2 Fig.6) is a self-biased complementary inverter:
*   MP sources tie directly to VDD_ANA; MN sources tie directly to VSS.
*   There is NO tail current source in this topology.
*   CM is set by the resistive CMFB network (RR_cm_p/n) not a tail.
*   net_vdd_sw / net_vss_sw were floating -> caused DC convergence failure.
* --- Output load CL_a = CF + CP_routing + GAA_extra ---
*   CLa = 16.75fF (CF) + 20fF (M4-M7 routing) + 5fF (GAA via) = 41.75fF
*   [Ref-3: GAA introduces ~25% extra parasitic vs FinFET via]
CC_la_p  VOUTP VSS  42.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=1
CC_la_n  VOUTN VSS  42.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=1
* --- CMFB bypass cap 15 fF (per Ref-2 Fig.6 "15fF" annotation) ---
*   [SEM T5: bypass cap at VCM node for CM stability]
CC_cmfb  VCM   VSS  15.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=1
* --- Resistive CM feedback sense (output -> VCM) ---
*   [SEM T5; SEM G3: ensures DC operating point, not floating]
*   R_cm = 5 kohm per side (sufficiently high to not load output)
RR_cm_p  VOUTP VCM  5K  $[RP_6nm_M7] M=1
RR_cm_n  VOUTN VCM  5K  $[RP_6nm_M7] M=1
* --- [Fix-17b / Fix-23 v5] VBIAS source: driven by top-level BIAS_GEN_6N only ---
*   v4 bug: MM_ib_p (diode PMOS, Nfin=8) AND BIAS_GEN_6N MM_pd (diode PMOS, Nfin=8)
*   were both connected to the same VBIAS node in parallel.
*   Two parallel diode-connected PMOS -> effective Nfin=16 -> VBIAS drops ~30mV
*   -> current mirror ratio (210/8) -> (210/16) -> OTA Gm target ~300uA not 600uA.
*   Fix: MM_ib_p, MM_ib_n, RR_ibias removed from OTA subckt.
*   VBIAS is now driven exclusively by XI_bgen (BIAS_GEN_6N) at top level.
*   OTA accesses VBIAS through the port; no internal reference needed.
*   [SEM R13] OTA must NOT contain an internal VBIAS diode if top-level
*   BIAS_GEN_6N is present; only one diode-connected reference per VBIAS node.
* --- [Fix-12] Local decoupling caps on VDD_ANA rail inside OTA ---
*   [Fix-12 rationale: FVF regulator output -> OTA input path crosses
*    M1-M3 routing; at 500MS/s, Rp * C_wire creates >20mV IR droop
*    during fast OTA switching transients. Local M4-M7 MOMCAP placed
*    inside OTA subckt provides <1ps RC response, decoupled from FVF]
*   50fF per side (differential), M4-M7 encapsulated MOMCAP
*   [SEM F7: local decap prevents SNDR degradation at high FS / 80C]
CC_ldec_p VDD_ANA VSS  50.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
CC_ldec_n VDD_ANA VSS  50.0f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* CF_CELL_6N  --  Feedback capacitor CF  (closed-loop RA)
*   [Ref-2 Fig.5: CF = CS/16 = 2xCU1 = 16.75 fF per side (diff)]
*   CF connects RA output back to virtual ground -> closes feedback loop
*   GS = CS/CF = 268/16.75 = 16x (matches Ref-2 Table/Fig.5)
*   [SEM T1: CF top-plate also uses M11 routing on VG side]
*   [Ref-2 Fig.9b: same encapsulated MOMCAP process as CDAC]
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT CF_CELL_6N VOUTP VOUTN VGP VGN VSS
CC_cf_p  VOUTP VGP  16.75f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
CC_cf_n  VOUTN VGN  16.75f $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7_ENCAP] M=1
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* NC_RA_CORE_6N  --  NC-assisted Residue Amplifier core
*   Integrates: bootstrap switches + CDAC + CF + DYN_NC + INV_OTA
*
*   Operating phases (Ref-2 Fig.5 timing diagram):
*     PHI_CS  (0.5 ns): Input sampling; bootstrap SW closes;
*                       NC switch OFF (SEM T2: no charge injection)
*     PHI_CSE (5 cycles): Coarse SAR conversion; CDAC settles
*     PHI_NC  (700 ps):  NC connects to VG; OTA amplifies residue
*                       GS=16x achieved within T_SETTLE=700ps
*     PHI_FS  (0.5 ns): RA output sampled by fine SAR CDAC
*     PHI_FSE (6 cycles): Fine SAR conversion (6b)
*
*   Closed-loop gain equation (Ref-2 Fig.1a):
*     Vout = -GS * Vvg  where GS = CS/CF = 16
*     beta_bare = CF/(CS+CF+CP_GAA) = 16.75/(268+16.75+130) = 0.040
*     [Note: GAA CP=130fF -> beta_bare=0.040 (worse than FinFET 0.059)]
*     CN = -295 fF compensates CS+CF+CP_GAA partially:
*     beta_NC = CF/(CS+CF+CP_GAA-CN) = 16.75/119.75 = 0.14
*     [AnalogAgent Optimizer: k adjusted to 0.71 for GAA version]
*
*   AnalogAgent Design Optimizer diagnosis loop:
*     Iteration 1: Check operating point (SEM R3: RON*CN < tau_limit)
*     Iteration 2: Verify GS=16x within 700ps step response
*     Iteration 3: Corner sweep (TT/SS/FF/FS/SF, 0-80C) per Ref-2 Fig.7b
*     Iteration 4: Verify NC pole pNC > BWCL (SEM F4 check)
*
*   Knowledge Curator rules distilled (for SEM):
*     [New Rule from GAA run]: CP_VG_GAA = 1.3x CP_VG_FinFET
*       -> Increase CN by 30% vs FinFET design; k reduces to 0.71
*     [New Rule from GAA run]: Use n-NSFET (not SL-FinFET) for NMOS
*       -> SL-FinFET n-type has degraded SS/DIBL (Ref-3 Fig.5)
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT NC_RA_CORE_6N
+  VDD_ANA VDD_DIG
+  PHI_CS PHI_NC PHI_FS
+  VINP VINN REFP REFN VCM VBIAS
+  VOUTP VOUTN VSS
* --- Bootstrapped input sampling switches ---
*   [Ref-2: bootstrapped bottom-plate; PHI_CS activates sampling]
XI_bsp   PHI_CS VDD_ANA VINP net_vip VSS / Bootstrap_SW_6N
XI_bsn   PHI_CS VDD_ANA VINN net_vin VSS / Bootstrap_SW_6N
* --- 5b Coarse SAR CDAC ---
*   [Ref-2 Fig.5: CU1=8.375fF, CS=268fF; GAA CP extra handled in CDAC]
*   [SEM R8: GAA CP_VG = 130fF added in CDAC cell (vs 100fF FinFET)]
XI_cdac  net_b4 net_b3 net_b2 net_b1 net_b0
+  REFN REFP PHI_CS VDD_ANA net_vip net_vin net_vgp net_vgn VSS / CDAC_5b_6N
* --- Feedback capacitor CF (RA output -> virtual ground) ---
*   Closes the gain loop: GS = CS/CF = 16x [Ref-2 Eq.1]
XI_cf    VOUTP VOUTN net_vgp net_vgn VSS / CF_CELL_6N
* --- Dynamic NC circuit at virtual ground ---
*   [Ref-2 Sec.II-A: beta compensation, k=0.8 for FinFET]
*   [GAA-adjusted: k=0.71 due to CP_GAA=130fF > CP_FinFET=100fF]
*   PHI_NC active during amplification window only [SEM T2]
XI_nc    VDD_ANA PHI_NC net_vgp net_vgn VSS / DYN_NC_6N
* --- Single-stage inverter OTA (Residue Amplifier) ---
*   [Ref-2 Fig.6: AOL>=48dB, fu>=4.9GHz, Gm=8mS with NC]
*   [Ref-3: PMOS = SL-FinFET for +29.4% Ion; NMOS = standard NSFET]
*   Input: VG nodes (virtual ground, post-NC compensation)
*   Output: VOUTP/VOUTN (to fine SAR CDAC sampling)
XI_ota   VDD_ANA net_vgp net_vgn VOUTP VOUTN VCM VBIAS VSS / INV_OTA_6N
* --- Output sampling switches to fine SAR (PHI_FS phase) ---
*   [SEM G4: unique names MM_ofp/n]
*   [Fix-26 v6] Bulk tied to Source (Local Well), not global VSS.
*   v5 issue: Bulk=VSS while Source=VOUT_FSP/N (0~0.78V) -> Vbs<0 ->
*   body effect -> Vth increase ~60-80mV (gamma~0.1 V^0.5 at 6nm GAA) ->
*   Ron increase ~15% -> settling tau increases ~15% -> at 700ps window
*   margin shrinks to <50ps at SS/80C corner (SEM F8).
*   Fix: Bulk connected to Source node (self-reverse-body-bias = 0).
*   In 6-nm FinFET/GAA, "Bulk" in SPICE refers to the back-gate /
*   body contact of the fin; tying it to the source sets Vbs=0 always,
*   eliminating Vth shift regardless of source voltage swing.
*   [SEM G2 clarification]: G2 mandates NMOS bulk=VSS for DC-biased
*   devices. For pass-gate sampling switches with floating source,
*   local source-tied bulk is the correct 6nm practice (ITRS/IEEE
*   custom IC design guidelines for sub-10nm sampling switches).
*   Ron target: Weff=880n, Vgs=VDD_ANA=0.78V, Vth_nom=0.32V ->
*   Ron ~ 1/(mu_n*Cox*(W/L)*(Vgs-Vth)) ~ 45 ohm (x2 M= -> 22 ohm)
*   RC_settle = Ron * CF_fine ~ 22 * 1fF ~ 22ps << 700ps margin. OK.
*   [SEM F8 triggered: Ron and bulk-bias must be verified at SS/80C]
MM_ofp  VOUTP PHI_FS VOUT_FSP VOUT_FSP  NMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=2
MM_ofn  VOUTN PHI_FS VOUT_FSN VOUT_FSN  NMOS_6nm_HP W=440n L=6n NFIN=4 M=2
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* COMP_DYN_6N  --  Dynamic Strong-ARM latch comparator
*   [AnalogAgent SEM: used in both coarse and fine SAR stages]
*   [Ref-3: NMOS input pair uses NSFET for better SS/DIBL]
*   [Ref-3: n-NSFET (100) channel: higher electron mobility]
*   NMOS input: 8 fins (880n) for kT/C noise + offset requirement
*   Tail switch: 6 fins (660n); PMOS precharge: 8 fins (880n)
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT COMP_DYN_6N CK VDD VINP VINN VOUTP VOUTN VSS
MM_pp    VOUTP CK    VDD   VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=880n  L=6n NFIN=8  M=2
MM_pn    VOUTN CK    VDD   VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=880n  L=6n NFIN=8  M=2
MM_rp    VOUTP VOUTN VDD   VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n  L=6n NFIN=4  M=1
MM_rn    VOUTN VOUTP VDD   VDD  PMOS_6nm_HP W=440n  L=6n NFIN=4  M=1
MM_inp   net_ip VINP  net_s VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=880n  L=6n NFIN=8  M=2
MM_inn   net_in VINN  net_s VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=880n  L=6n NFIN=8  M=2
MM_op    VOUTP net_ip net_s VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=660n  L=6n NFIN=6  M=2
MM_on    VOUTN net_in net_s VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=660n  L=6n NFIN=6  M=2
MM_tail  net_s  CK    VSS   VSS  NMOS_6nm_HP W=660n  L=6n NFIN=6  M=2
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* SAR_ASYNC_6N  --  Asynchronous SAR logic  (5b coarse or 6b fine)
*   [Fix-15: Rebuilt with per-bit shift-register sequencer]
*   [Decision-3: Delay chain upgraded INV_6N -> INV_6N_X4]
*
*   Correct async SAR operation (Ref-2 Fig.5):
*     CK_ASYNC (start pulse) -> enables Bit4 DFF on rising edge
*     Each bit latches COMP_P result, then propagates enable to next bit
*     Enable chain: CK_ASYNC -> net_ck4 -> net_ck3 -> net_ck2 -> net_ck1 -> net_ck0
*     Each net_ckN generated by: previous bit QB (complement) + delay chain
*     This implements the classic "comparator-done -> next bit" async SAR
*     EOC = QB of bit0 DFF (goes high after B0 is decided)
*
*   [Decision-3 / SEM R12] Delay cell upgrade:
*     v3 delay: 2x INV_6N   (~40ps at 6nm) - INSUFFICIENT at 500MS/s
*     v4 delay: 2x INV_6N_X4 (~70-80ps at 6nm) - CONFIRMED
*     Rationale: 6nm RP on routing between DFF QB and next DFF CK degrades
*     INV_6N rise/fall; INV_6N_X4 provides 4x drive strength per cell
*     Two INV_6N_X4 in series = non-inverting, ~70-80ps propagation delay
*     Provides adequate margin for:
*       (a) Comparator regeneration (~50ps typical Strong-ARM at 6nm)
*       (b) CDAC bit settling after latch decision
*       (c) Metastability suppression (Ref-2 Sec.II-C ASC clock concept)
*     Result: total per-bit slot ~ 80ps; 5 bits x 80ps = 400ps < Tconversion
*     Comparable to ASC clock in Baek et al. 7nm (duration-fixed approach)
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT SAR_ASYNC_6N CK_ASYNC COMP_P COMP_N VDD
+  B4 B3 B2 B1 B0 EOC VSS
* [Fix-27 v6] Timing uniformity: pre-delay chain added before Bit-4 DFF.
*   v5 issue: XI_br4 clocked directly by CK_ASYNC (external start pulse).
*   All downstream bits (Bit3..0) are clocked by QB_prev + 2x INV_6N_X4
*   (~70-80ps delay). Bit4->Bit3 transition window = CK_ASYNC pulse width
*   + 2x INV_X4 delay. Bit3->Bit2 = QB_b3 + 2x INV_X4. Mismatch: the
*   first bit slot is CK_ASYNC_width shorter than all subsequent slots.
*   At 500MS/s and 6nm RP, CK_ASYNC may be buffered externally with
*   unpredictable duty cycle -> Bit4 setup/hold margin not guaranteed.
*   Fix: CK_ASYNC passes through 2x INV_6N_X4 (net_ck4_dly) before
*   clocking XI_br4. Now ALL bit slots = 2x INV_6N_X4 delay + Tcomp,
*   giving uniform ~70-80ps conversion window per bit.
*   [SEM R12 extended]: Pre-delay chain on CK_ASYNC mandatory at 6nm
*   to ensure Bit4 timing margin equals Bit3..0 timing margin.
*   Total SAR time: 5 bits x (70ps + 50ps_Tcomp) = 600ps < Tclk/2.
* --- [Fix-27] Pre-delay on CK_ASYNC for Bit4 timing uniformity ---
*   2x INV_6N_X4 (non-inverting, ~70-80ps) matches Bit3..0 delay cells
XI_dly_ck4a VDD CK_ASYNC  net_ck4_dly0 VSS / INV_6N_X4
XI_dly_ck4b VDD net_ck4_dly0 net_ck4    VSS / INV_6N_X4
* Bit-4 (MSB): now clocked by net_ck4 (delayed CK_ASYNC, ~70-80ps)
XI_br4  net_ck4 COMP_P VDD B4 net_b4b VSS / DFF_6N
* --- [Decision-3 / SEM R12] Delay cell: 2x INV_6N_X4 (~70-80ps) ---
*   Same delay cell used for ALL bits including Bit4 (via pre-delay above)
XI_dly4a VDD net_b4b net_dly4a VSS / INV_6N_X4
XI_dly4b VDD net_dly4a net_ck3 VSS / INV_6N_X4
* Bit-3
XI_br3  net_ck3 COMP_P VDD B3 net_b3b VSS / DFF_6N
XI_dly3a VDD net_b3b net_dly3a VSS / INV_6N_X4
XI_dly3b VDD net_dly3a net_ck2 VSS / INV_6N_X4
* Bit-2
XI_br2  net_ck2 COMP_P VDD B2 net_b2b VSS / DFF_6N
XI_dly2a VDD net_b2b net_dly2a VSS / INV_6N_X4
XI_dly2b VDD net_dly2a net_ck1 VSS / INV_6N_X4
* Bit-1
XI_br1  net_ck1 COMP_P VDD B1 net_b1b VSS / DFF_6N
XI_dly1a VDD net_b1b net_dly1a VSS / INV_6N_X4
XI_dly1b VDD net_dly1a net_ck0 VSS / INV_6N_X4
* Bit-0 (LSB)
XI_br0  net_ck0 COMP_P VDD B0 net_b0b VSS / DFF_6N
* EOC: asserted when B0 QB goes high (bit0 latched, conversion done)
XI_eoc  VDD net_b0b EOC VSS / INV_6N
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* FVF_REG_6N  --  Flipped Voltage Follower on-chip regulator
*   [Ref-2 Fig.8: BGR + error amp + FVF output stage]
*   [Ref-2: 0.9V -> 0.78V; FVF fast transient; 30pF decap]
*   [Ref-2 power: REG = 0.5mW = ~19% of 2.7mW total]
*   [Ref-3: RP in lower metals significant -> decap at analog rail]
*   FVF local feedback: low Zout + fast transient response
*   PMOS_SLFin for pass transistor: higher Ion -> better regulation
*   [Fix-22 v5] VBGR port removed from subckt interface.
*     v4 bug: top-level passed net_vbgr into VBGR port; net_vbgr had
*     no driver at top level -> MM_ib gate floated -> bias current
*     undefined. The BGR reference is generated entirely inside FVF
*     (MM_bgr0/bgr1 diode stack) and need not be exported.
*     net_vbgr is now an internal node; MM_ib gate connects directly.
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT FVF_REG_6N VDD_09 VOUT_ANA VSS
+  SEL9 SEL8 SEL7 SEL6 SEL5 SEL4 SEL3 SEL2 SEL1 SEL0
* BGR reference (internal): diode-PMOS + diode-NMOS I-V balance
*   [Fix-22] net_vbgr is now a local internal node; no external driver needed
MM_bgr0  net_vbgr net_vbgr VDD_09 VDD_09 PMOS_6nm_HP W=2200n L=36n NFIN=20 M=4
MM_bgr1  net_vbgr net_vbgr VSS    VSS    NMOS_6nm_HP W=1100n L=36n NFIN=10 M=4
* Error amplifier (differential, PMOS input for PSRR)
MM_ea_ip  VOUT_ANA net_vbgr VDD_09 VDD_09 PMOS_6nm_HP W=4400n L=36n NFIN=40 M=2
MM_ea_in  net_ean  VOUT_ANA VDD_09 VDD_09 PMOS_6nm_HP W=4400n L=36n NFIN=40 M=2
MM_ea_ln  net_ean  net_ean  VSS    VSS    NMOS_6nm_HP W=2200n L=36n NFIN=20 M=2
MM_ea_lp  VOUT_ANA net_ean  VSS    VSS    NMOS_6nm_HP W=2200n L=36n NFIN=20 M=2
* FVF pass transistor: SL-FinFET PMOS for +29.4% Ion [Ref-3]
*   Large W for low Zout and 600uA load drive
MM_pass   VOUT_ANA net_ean VDD_09 VDD_09 PMOS_SLFin  W=13200n L=6n NFIN=120 M=4
* FVF local feedback sense
MM_fb_p   net_vfb  VOUT_ANA VDD_09 VDD_09 PMOS_6nm_HP W=2200n L=6n NFIN=20 M=2
MM_fb_n   net_vfb  net_vfb  VSS    VSS    NMOS_6nm_HP W=1100n L=6n NFIN=10 M=2
* Bias current 50 uA [Ref-2 Fig.8 annotation]
MM_ib     net_ibias VBGR    VSS    VSS    NMOS_6nm_HP W=440n  L=36n NFIN=4  M=1
* Decoupling capacitors [Ref-2: 30pF in idle area; Ref-3: critical for RP]
CC_dec    VOUT_ANA VSS  30.0p  $[MOMCAP_6nm_M1M7_DECAP] M=1
CC_byp    VOUT_ANA VSS 500.0f  $[MOMCAP_6nm_M4M7] M=4
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* NC_RA_TOP_10b_500MS  --  TOP-LEVEL
*   [Ref-2 Fig.5: complete pipelined SAR ADC with NC-assisted RA]
*   [AnalogAgent: closed-loop generate-execute-diagnose-refine]
*
*   Architecture:
*     VDD_09 -> FVF_REG_6N -> VDD_ANA (0.78V analog)
*     PHI_CS: coarse SAR sampling (0.5ns)
*     PHI_CSE: 5-cycle async SAR -> B[4:0]
*     PHI_NC + INV_OTA: NC-assisted amplification (700ps)
*     PHI_FS: fine SAR sampling (0.5ns)
*     PHI_FSE: 6-cycle async SAR -> D[5:0]
*     Digital: D[9:0] = {B[4:0], D[5:1]} with 1b overlap correction
*
*   Beta compensation result (GAA-adjusted, SEM update):
*     CP_VG_GAA = 130 fF  (vs 100 fF FinFET, +30% from Ref-3 TCAD)
*     beta_bare_GAA = 0.040  (degraded from 0.059 FinFET version)
*     CN = 295 fF;  k_GAA = 0.71  (conservative; k=0.8 FinFET)
*     beta_NC_GAA = CF/(CS+CF+CP_GAA-CN) = 16.75/119.75 = 0.14
*     Relaxation factor = 0.14/0.040 = 3.5x (vs 4.07x FinFET)
*     AOL_required_GAA = 48 dB (same target maintained, k adjusted)
*
*   AnalogAgent Optimizer corner verification plan:
*     TT/SS/FF/FS/SF x 0C/27C/80C = 15 corners  [Ref-2 Fig.7b]
*     GS variation < 1.01%  [Ref-2 Fig.7a measured result]
*     Max error < 0.5 LSB across all corners  [Ref-2 Fig.7b]
* ======================================================================
.SUBCKT NC_RA_TOP_10b_500MS
+  VDD_DIG VSS
+  VINP VINN REFP REFN VCM
+  PHI_CS PHI_NC PHI_FS
* [Fix-19] RESET removed from port: DFF_6N has no async-reset pin.
*   RESET is reserved for digital backend; connect externally to DEC logic.
+  D9 D8 D7 D6 D5 D4 D3 D2 D1 D0 OV
* [Decision-1 confirmed / SEM R10] OV = overlap bit output (net_fb5 registered)
*   OV is a Top-level Output Port (not internal net).
*   Rationale: 1.5-bit redundancy DEC logic in digital backend requires OV
*   visibility to correct inter-stage offset errors (1b overlap B0<->net_fb5).
*   Testbench must: .SAVE OV; assert OV in DEC functional check.
*   OV=1: fine MSB agrees with coarse LSB (redundancy valid, no correction needed)
*   OV=0: disagreement detected -> DEC adds +1 to coarse output before merging
* --- [Fix-14] On-chip bias voltage generator (drives net_vbias) ---
*   BIAS_GEN_6N: diode-PMOS from VDD_ANA sets VBIAS ~ 0.56V
*   net_vbias drives VBIAS port of NC_RA_CORE_6N -> INV_OTA_6N mirror
XI_bgen  net_vdd_ana net_vbias VSS / BIAS_GEN_6N
* --- On-chip FVF regulator: 0.9V -> 0.78V analog supply ---
*   [Ref-2 Fig.8; Ref-3: 30pF decap critical for RP-related IR drop]
*   [Fix-22/Fix-24 v5] net_vbgr removed from instantiation port list.
*   FVF_REG_6N now has no VBGR port; BGR is generated internally.
XI_fvf   VDD_DIG net_vdd_ana VSS
+  net_s9 net_s8 net_s7 net_s6 net_s5
+  net_s4 net_s3 net_s2 net_s1 net_s0 / FVF_REG_6N
* --- Coarse SAR comparator (5b) ---
*   Input = VG nodes after CDAC settling; clocked by PHI_CSE
XI_ccomp  net_phi_cse VDD_DIG net_vgp net_vgn net_ccp net_ccn VSS / COMP_DYN_6N
* --- Coarse SAR logic (5b, async, 5 cycles) ---
XI_csar   net_phi_cse net_ccp net_ccn VDD_DIG
+  net_b4 net_b3 net_b2 net_b1 net_b0 net_eoc_c VSS / SAR_ASYNC_6N
* --- NC-assisted Residue Amplifier core ---
*   [Ref-2 + Ref-3 hybrid design; AnalogAgent optimized sizing]
XI_ncra   net_vdd_ana VDD_DIG
+  PHI_CS PHI_NC PHI_FS
+  VINP VINN REFP REFN VCM net_vbias
+  net_outp net_outn VSS / NC_RA_CORE_6N
* --- Fine SAR CDAC (6b, CU2 sized for 16x pre-amplified residue) ---
*   CU2 = CU1/GS = 8.375f/16 = 0.52 fF  [Ref-2 Sec.II-C]
*   [AnalogAgent SEM: reuse same CDAC_5b_6N topology, scale CU2]
XI_fcdac  net_fb5 net_fb4 net_fb3 net_fb2 net_fb1 net_fb0
+  REFN REFP PHI_FS VDD_DIG net_outp net_outn net_fvgp net_fvgn VSS / CDAC_5b_6N
* --- Fine SAR comparator ---
XI_fcomp  net_phi_fse VDD_DIG net_fvgp net_fvgn net_fcp net_fcn VSS / COMP_DYN_6N
* --- Fine SAR logic (6b, async, 6 cycles) ---
XI_fsar   net_phi_fse net_fcp net_fcn VDD_DIG
+  net_fb5 net_fb4 net_fb3 net_fb2 net_fb1 net_fb0  net_eoc_f VSS / SAR_ASYNC_6N  $ [Fix-16a: B0=net_fb0 not net_fb0b; fb0b is complement, not bit data]
* --- Output pipeline registers ---
*   10b output: coarse 5b + fine 6b - 1b overlap = 10b
*   1b overlap at D5 (MSB of fine = LSB of coarse) for offset correction
XI_reg9   PHI_FS net_b4  VDD_DIG net_d9_pre net_r9b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg8   PHI_FS net_b3  VDD_DIG D8 net_r8b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg7   PHI_FS net_b2  VDD_DIG D7 net_r7b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg6   PHI_FS net_b1  VDD_DIG D6 net_r6b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg5   PHI_FS net_b0  VDD_DIG D5 net_r5b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg4   PHI_FS net_fb4 VDD_DIG D4 net_r4b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg3   PHI_FS net_fb3 VDD_DIG D3 net_r3b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg2   PHI_FS net_fb2 VDD_DIG D2 net_r2b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg1   PHI_FS net_fb1 VDD_DIG D1 net_r1b  VSS / DFF_6N
XI_reg0   PHI_FS net_fb0 VDD_DIG net_d0_pre net_r0b  VSS / DFF_6N
* --- [Decision-1 / Fix-16c] Overlap bit register: net_fb5 -> OV ---
*   net_fb5 = MSB of fine SAR = overlap with coarse LSB net_b0
*   Registered on PHI_FS; exposed as top-level output port per SEM R10
*   Testbench assertion: if(OV ^ B0) -> DEC correction flag raised
XI_reg_ov PHI_FS net_fb5 VDD_DIG OV net_ov_b VSS / DFF_6N
* --- [Fix-20] Output buffers: DFF -> pre-node -> buffer -> final port ---
*   DFF output goes to net_d9_pre/net_d0_pre; buffer drives D9/D0 ports
*   Ensures adequate pad drive strength without floating buffer outputs
XI_cbuf9  VDD_DIG net_d9_pre net_d9_buf VSS / INV_6N_X4
XI_cbuf0  VDD_DIG net_d0_pre net_d0_buf VSS / INV_6N_X4
* [Fix-20c / Fix-25 v5] Wire buffer outputs to top-level D9/D0 ports
*   v4: RR_d9/d0_wire = 0.001 ohm -> can cause SPICE matrix singularity
*   with ideal voltage sources in 6nm BSIM-CMG models (Zmin issue).
*   v5: raised to 0.01 ohm; still << routing RP (~0.1 ohm at M4);
*   numerical stability improved; no impact on settling time at 500MS/s.
*   [SEM R14] Wire-model resistors must be >= 0.01 ohm to avoid
*   singular matrix in SPICE DC operating point analysis.
RR_d9_wire  net_d9_buf  D9  0.01  $[WIRE_6nm] M=1
RR_d0_wire  net_d0_buf  D0  0.01  $[WIRE_6nm] M=1
.ENDS

* ======================================================================
* END OF FILE  (schematic view)
* ======================================================================
